For closed shell molecules near equilibrium, CCSD provides a robust ansatz for molecular simulations. Early efforts to combine size extensivity and variationality were pioneered by Bartlett, Kutzelnigg, and coworkers23–25. In this context, a unitary variant of coupled cluster theory (UCCSD) was defined by replacing the excitation operators with an anti-Hermitian sum of excitation and de-excitation operators:4\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
