The above discussion described the Trotter expansion as an approximation to UCCGSD. However, as recognized previously7,35, if the parameters are optimized after the Trotterization, this is not so much an approximation to UCC as it is a wholly unique ansatz. In fact, the exact FCI solution could be obtained by simply going to an nth order Trotterized form of UCCSD and allowing the different parameter replicas to vary independently. This is due to the fact that n-body interactions can be described as products of one- and two-body interactions. The exact (FCI) quantum state can thus be represented as an arbitrarily long product of one- and two-body operators,7\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
